Based on the information provided in the incident description and the CERT.br website, I have categorized the incident as follows:

1. Arms: status/pacotes/bytes, onde status é "open", e pacotes/bytes indicam o tamanho da resposta recebida, em pacotes/bytes;
2. Description: alerta de serviço Apple Remote Desktop (ARD) abusado no equipamento;
3. Explanation: the serviço ARMS is part of the service Apple Remote Desktop and it is used for remote desktop services to access macOS devices via UDP. It can be abused by attackers to cause damages like denial-of-service attacks or DDoS amplification. The explanation explains why this category should be selected as appropriate based on the problem description and classification criteria.
